hwEthernetTable.name: hwEthernetTable
hwEthernetTable.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the Ethernet interface. This table lists the physical attributes of various Ethernet interfaces.

hwEthernetEntry.name: hwEthernetEntry
hwEthernetEntry.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the Ethernet interface. This table lists the physical attributes of various Ethernet interfaces.

hwEthernetIfIndex.name: hwEthernetIfIndex
hwEthernetIfIndex.description: Interface index(es) of port(s) present on the device .

hwEthernetLoopback.name: hwEthernetLoopback
hwEthernetLoopback.description: The local loopback of an Ethernet interface is used to test the interface itself. If an interface works in a normal situation, disable the local loopback. By default, stopLoopback is used.

hwEthernetPortType.name: hwEthernetPortType
hwEthernetPortType.description: Indicates the type of the Ethernet interface: an optical interface or an electrical interface.

hwEthernetSpeedSet.name: hwEthernetSpeedSet
hwEthernetSpeedSet.description: Indicates the speed of the Ethernet interface. This parameter takes effect only on some Ethernet electrical interfaces rather than optical interfaces. The parameter can be 10 M, 100 M, 1000 M, 10000 M,40000 M,20000 M,2500 M,5000 M.

hwEthernetDuplex.name: hwEthernetDuplex
hwEthernetDuplex.description: Indicates the duplex mode of the Ethernet interface. An electrical Ethernet interface can work in half-duplex mode or full-duplex mode. An optical Ethernet can work only in full-duplex mode.

hwEthernetNegotiation.name: hwEthernetNegotiation
hwEthernetNegotiation.description: Indicates the auto-negotiation mode of the Ethernet electrical interface. By default, auto-negotiation is enabled. The three objects, hwEthernetSpeedSet, hwEthernetDuplex, and hwEthernetNegotiation are associated with each other. If the auto-negotiation of hwEthernetNegotiation is enabled, the values of hwEthernetSpeedSet and hwEthernetDuplex are auto-negotiated. If hwEthernetSpeedSet is set to a certain value, hwEthernetDuplex is modified to the default value full, and hwEthernetNegotiation is automatically changed to disable. If the auto-negotiation of hwEthernetNegotiation is enabled, hwEthernetDuplex cannot be set.

hwEthernetPortTypeOperate.name: hwEthernetPortTypeOperate
hwEthernetPortTypeOperate.description: Indicates the link type of the Ethernet interface. The type can be optical link or electrical link. This parameter takes effect only on specific Ethernet interfaces.

hwEthernetClock.name: hwEthernetClock
hwEthernetClock.description: Indicates the mode of the clock. The mode can be master or slave. By default, the mode of a clock is slave. This parameter takes effect only on the WAN board.

hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode.name: hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode
hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode.description: Before the 10 GE WAN board processes packets, the overhead byte must be configured on the interface. The overhead byte for the SDH frame, j0: Set section trace byte The default value is j016ByteMode(2):hwEthernetFlagJ0Trace:NetEngine

hwEthernetFlagJ0Value.name: hwEthernetFlagJ0Value
hwEthernetFlagJ0Value.description: j01ByteMode Value. When hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode is set to j01ByteMode, this parameter takes effect.

hwEthernetFlagJ0Trace.name: hwEthernetFlagJ0Trace
hwEthernetFlagJ0Trace.description: Set section trace byte. When hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode or j064ByteOrNullMode, this variable takes effect. When hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode, this variable is up to 15 characters trace byte. When hwEthernetFlagJ0Mode is set to j064ByteOrNullMode, this variable is up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode.name: hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode
hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. j1:sets path trace byte. The default value is j116ByteMode(2) hwEthernetFlagJ1Trace NetEngine.

hwEthernetFlagJ1Value.name: hwEthernetFlagJ1Value
hwEthernetFlagJ1Value.description: j11ByteMode Value. When hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode is set to j11ByteMode, this parameter takes effect.

hwEthernetFlagJ1Trace.name: hwEthernetFlagJ1Trace
hwEthernetFlagJ1Trace.description: Set path trace byte. When hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode is set to j116ByteMode or j164ByteOrNullMode, this variable takes effect. When hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode is set to j116ByteMode, this variable is up to 15 characters trace byte. When hwEthernetFlagJ1Mode is set to j164ByteOrNullMode, this variable is up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwEthernetFlagC2Value.name: hwEthernetFlagC2Value
hwEthernetFlagC2Value.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. c2: indicates the signal label byte. It is a hexdecimal value ranging from 00 to FF. The default value is 0x02.

hwEthernetUpHoldTime.name: hwEthernetUpHoldTime
hwEthernetUpHoldTime.description: Indicates the response time to the event that the port turns Up. The units of hwEthernetUpHoldTime is millisecond.

hwEthernetDownHoldTime.name: hwEthernetDownHoldTime
hwEthernetDownHoldTime.description: Indicates the response time to the event that the port turns Down. The units of hwEthernetDownHoldTime is millisecond.

hwEthernetSubinterfaceStatisticEnable.name: hwEthernetSubinterfaceStatisticEnable
hwEthernetSubinterfaceStatisticEnable.description: Enable the statistical function of the sub-interface.

hwEthernetFlowControl.name: hwEthernetFlowControl
hwEthernetFlowControl.description: Set flow control of this port.

hwEthernetOffline.name: hwEthernetOffline
hwEthernetOffline.description: Set Line protocol state to down of this port.

hwEthernetSetTransferMode.name: hwEthernetSetTransferMode
hwEthernetSetTransferMode.description: Set transfer mode of this port.

hwEthernetJumboframeMaxLength.name: hwEthernetJumboframeMaxLength
hwEthernetJumboframeMaxLength.description: Set the jumboframe max length of this port.

hwEthernetPortMode.name: hwEthernetPortMode
hwEthernetPortMode.description: Indicates combo mode of this port.

hwEthernetNegotiationMode.name: hwEthernetNegotiationMode
hwEthernetNegotiationMode.description: Set negotiation-mode for phy of electronic GE port.The mode is uesed for synchronizing clock.

hwPosTable.name: hwPosTable
hwPosTable.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the POS interface. This table lists the physical attributes of the POS interface.

hwPosEntry.name: hwPosEntry
hwPosEntry.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the POS interface. This table lists the physical attributes of the POS interface.

hwPosIfIndex.name: hwPosIfIndex
hwPosIfIndex.description: Interface index(es) of port(s) present on the device .

hwPosLinkProtocol.name: hwPosLinkProtocol
hwPosLinkProtocol.description: Indicates the link layer protocol of the POS interface. By default, on a POS interface, PPP serves as the link layer protocol.

hwPosFrameFormat.name: hwPosFrameFormat
hwPosFrameFormat.description: Indicates the frame type of the POS interface. By default, the frame type of the POS interface is SDH. This variable identifies whether a SONET or a SDH signal is used across this interface.

hwPosLoopback.name: hwPosLoopback
hwPosLoopback.description: The local loopback of a POS interface is used to test the interface itself. If an interface works in a normal situation, disable the local loopback. By default, stopLoopback is used.

hwPosScramble.name: hwPosScramble
hwPosScramble.description: Indicates the scramble function of payload. By default, the scramble function of payload is enabled.

hwPosClock.name: hwPosClock
hwPosClock.description: Indicates whether the clock is in master mode or slave mode. By default, the clock is in slave mode.

hwPosCrcVerifyCode.name: hwPosCrcVerifyCode
hwPosCrcVerifyCode.description: Indicates the length of the CRC verity code. The default value is 32.

hwPosFlagJ0Mode.name: hwPosFlagJ0Mode
hwPosFlagJ0Mode.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. j0: sets section trace byte. The default value is j016ByteMode(2);hwPosFlagJ0Trace:NetEngine.

hwPosFlagJ0Value.name: hwPosFlagJ0Value
hwPosFlagJ0Value.description: Indicates the value of j01ByteMode. When hwPosFlagJ0Mode is set to j01ByteMode, hwPosFlagJ0Value takes effect.

hwPosFlagJ0Trace.name: hwPosFlagJ0Trace
hwPosFlagJ0Trace.description: Set section trace byte. When hwPosFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode or j064ByteOrNullMode, this variable takes effect. When hwPosFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode, the value of this variable is up to 15 characters trace byte. When hwPosFlagJ0Mode is set to j064ByteOrNullMode, the value of this variable is up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwPosFlagJ1Mode.name: hwPosFlagJ1Mode

hwPosFlagJ1Trace.name: hwPosFlagJ1Trace

When hwPosFlagJ1Mode is set to j116ByteMode, this variable is up to 15 characters trace byte. When hwPosFlagJ1Mode is set to j164ByteOrNullMode, this variable is up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwPosFlagC2Value.name: hwPosFlagC2Value
hwPosFlagC2Value.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. c2: indicates the signal label byte. It is a hexdecimal value ranging from 00 to FF. The default value is 0x02.

hwCposTable.name: hwCposTable
hwCposTable.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the CPOS interface. This table lists the physical attributes of the CPOS interface.

hwCposEntry.name: hwCposEntry
hwCposEntry.description: Indicates the physical attributes of the CPOS interface. This table lists the physical attributes of the CPOS interface.

hwCposIfIndex.name: hwCposIfIndex
hwCposIfIndex.description: Interface index(es) of port(s) present on the device .

hwCposClock.name: hwCposClock
hwCposClock.description: Indicates whether the clock is in master mode or slave mode. By default, the clock is in slave mode.

hwCposFrameFormat.name: hwCposFrameFormat
hwCposFrameFormat.description: Indicates the frame type of the CPOS interface. By default, the frame type of the CPOS interface is SDH.

hwCposMultiplex.name: hwCposMultiplex
hwCposMultiplex.description: Indicates the multiplex mode of the AUG. By default, the multiplex mode of the AUG is au-4.

hwCposLoopback.name: hwCposLoopback
hwCposLoopback.description: Indicates the loopback function of the CPOS interface. By default, the loopback function is disabled.

hwCposFlagJ0Mode.name: hwCposFlagJ0Mode
hwCposFlagJ0Mode.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. j0: sets section trace byte. The default value is j016ByteMode(2);hwCposFlagJ0Trace NetEngine.

hwCposFlagJ0Value.name: hwCposFlagJ0Value
hwCposFlagJ0Value.description: j01ByteMode Value . When hwCposFlagJ0Mode is set to j01ByteMode, hwCposFlagJ0Value takes effect.

hwCposFlagJ0Trace.name: hwCposFlagJ0Trace
hwCposFlagJ0Trace.description: Set section trace byte. When hwCposFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode or j064ByteOrNullMode, this variable takes effect. When hwCposFlagJ0Mode is set to j016ByteMode, this variable is up to 15 characters trace byte. When hwCposFlagJ0Mode is set to j064ByteOrNullMode, this variable is up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwCposFlagJ1Mode.name: hwCposFlagJ1Mode
hwCposFlagJ1Mode.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. j1: sets path trace byte. The default value is j116ByteMode(2);hwCposFlagJ1Trace NetEngine.

hwCposFlagJ1Value.name: hwCposFlagJ1Value
hwCposFlagJ1Value.description: Indicates the value of j11ByteMode. When hwCposFlagJ1Mode is set to j11ByteMode, hwCposFlagJ1Value takes effect.

hwCposFlagJ1Trace.name: hwCposFlagJ1Trace

When hwCposFlagJ1Mode is set to j164ByteOrNullMode, this variable is a string up to 64 characters trace byte.

hwCposB1SdAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of B1 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposB1ExcAlarmThreshold.name: hwCposB1ExcAlarmThreshold
hwCposB1ExcAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of B1 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposB2SdAlarmThreshold.name: hwCposB2SdAlarmThreshold
hwCposB2SdAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of B2 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposB2ExcAlarmThreshold.name: hwCposB2ExcAlarmThreshold
hwCposB2ExcAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of B2 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposB3SdAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of B3 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposLpBipExcAlarmThreshold.name: hwCposLpBipExcAlarmThreshold
hwCposLpBipExcAlarmThreshold.description: The threshold of BIP2 threshold crossing alarm.

hwCposHighPathNumber.name: hwCposHighPathNumber
hwCposHighPathNumber.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. c2: indicates the signal label byte. It is a hexdecimal value ranging from 00 to FF. The default value is 22(0x16).

hwCposLowPathNumber.name: hwCposLowPathNumber
hwCposLowPathNumber.description: Indicates the overhead byte of the SDH frame. c2: indicates the signal label byte. It is a hexdecimal value ranging from 00 to FF. The default value is 22(0x16).

hwCposMappingMode.name: hwCposMappingMode
hwCposMappingMode.description: Indicates the mapping mode of cpos port, default if h-mode(1).

hwCposRxJ0Value.name: hwCposRxJ0Value
hwCposRxJ0Value.description: Indicates the received J0 value of 1-byte mode.

hwCposRxJ1Value.name: hwCposRxJ1Value
hwCposRxJ1Value.description: Indicates the received J1 value of 1-byte mode.

hwCposRxJ0Trace.name: hwCposRxJ0Trace
hwCposRxJ0Trace.description: Indicates the received J0 characters of 16-byte or 64-byte mode.

hwCposRxJ1Trace.name: hwCposRxJ1Trace
hwCposRxJ1Trace.description: Indicates the received J1 characters of 16-byte or 64-byte mode.

hwCposVc4Flag.name: hwCposVc4Flag
hwCposVc4Flag.description: The value of this object identifies whether a VC4 channel can be created on the CPOS interface. 0 indicates that no VC4 channel can be created on the CPOS interface. 1 indicates that a VC4 channel can be created but has not been created on the CPOS interface. 2 indicates that a VC4 channel can be created and has been created on the CPOS interface.

hwPortPhysicalHpIndex.name: hwPortPhysicalHpIndex
hwPortPhysicalHpIndex.description: Indicates the higher order path number.

hwPortPhysicalLpIndex.name: hwPortPhysicalLpIndex
hwPortPhysicalLpIndex.description: Indicates the low order path number.

hwCposRxJ2Value.name: hwCposRxJ2Value

hwCposRxJ2Trace.name: hwCposRxJ2Trace

hwDs0ChannelBundleTable.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleTable
hwDs0ChannelBundleTable.description: This table is used to bundle timeslots of CE1/CT1 interfaces.

hwDs0ChannelBundleEntry.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleEntry
hwDs0ChannelBundleEntry.description: This table is used to bundle timeslots of CE1/CT1 interfaces.

hwDs0ChannelBundleParentIfIndex.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleParentIfIndex
hwDs0ChannelBundleParentIfIndex.description: Indicates the index of the parent interface.

hwDs0ChannelBundleId.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleId
hwDs0ChannelBundleId.description: Indicates the index number of the channel set.

hwDs0ChannelBundleIfIndex.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleIfIndex
hwDs0ChannelBundleIfIndex.description: Indicates the index of the serial interface formed by the timeslot binding.

hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlots.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlots
hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlots.description: Indicates the number of the range of the timeslot to be bound. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 31. Multiple timeslots are separated by ','. The range of timeslot is expressed by using '-'. For E1 card mode: If the timeslots are '0-31', it means unframed format, If the timeslots are '0-30', it means framed format, For T1 card mode: If the timeslots are '0-23', it means unframed format, If the timeslots are '0-22', it means framed format, and hwDs0ChannelBundleDs1ChannelId and hwDs0ChannelBundleId should be zero.

hwDs0ChannelBundleSpeed.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleSpeed
hwDs0ChannelBundleSpeed.description: Configures the mode to configure the timeslots. If the parameter 56 k is selected, the timeslots are bound in the mode of N x 56 kbit/s. If the parameter 64 k is selected, the timeslots are bound in the mode of N x 64 kbit/s. If the parameter 150336 k is selected, the interface is used for remarking the CEP interface. The default value is 64kbit/s.

hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlot0.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlot0
hwDs0ChannelBundleTimeSlot0.description: Indicates the timeslot0 to be bound or a single channel. The ture value indicates it will be create TDM channel.

hwDs0ChannelBundleIsMasterPW.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleIsMasterPW
hwDs0ChannelBundleIsMasterPW.description: Indicates if the pw configed on this port is master pw.

hwDs0ChannelBundleMasterPWStatus.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleMasterPWStatus
hwDs0ChannelBundleMasterPWStatus.description: Indicates the status of master pw.

hwDs0ChannelBundleRowStatus.name: hwDs0ChannelBundleRowStatus
hwDs0ChannelBundleRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create or delete an object.

hwDs1Table.name: hwDs1Table
hwDs1Table.description: This table lists all E1/CE1 interfaces or T1/CT1 interfaces. After the mode of E3/CE3 interfaces or T3/CT3 interfaces is set to channelized, this table can be used to create E1/CE1, or T1/CT1, or E3/CE3, or T3/CT3 interfaces.

hwDs1Entry.name: hwDs1Entry
hwDs1Entry.description: This table lists all E1/CE1 interfaces or T1/CT1 interfaces. After the mode of E3/CE3 interfaces or T3/CT3 interfaces is set to channelized, this table can be used to create E1/CE1, or T1/CT1, or E3/CE3, or T3/CT3 interfaces.

hwDs1ParentIfIndex.name: hwDs1ParentIfIndex
hwDs1ParentIfIndex.description: Indicates the index of the parent interface.

hwDs1ChannelType.name: hwDs1ChannelType
hwDs1ChannelType.description: Indicates the interface type. The type can be E1/CE1 or T1/CT1.

hwDs1IfType.name: hwDs1IfType
hwDs1IfType.description: Indicates the interface tyep. e3: is multiplexed by CE3 interfaces. t3: is multiplexed by CT3 interfaces. cpos: is multiplexed by CPOS interfaces. atm: is multiplexed by ATM interfaces. none: indicates the physical interface. default:none

hwDs1Channelized.name: hwDs1Channelized
hwDs1Channelized.description: Indicates the working mode of the interface. true: indicates the channelized mode. false: indicates the clear channel mode. The default is true.

hwDs1CodeType.name: hwDs1CodeType
hwDs1CodeType.description: Indicates the code type of the interface. ami: is short for Alternate Mark Inversion. hdb3: is short for High Density Bipolar of Order 3. b8zs: is short for Bipolar with 8-Zero Substitution. none: is not supported

hwDs1Clock.name: hwDs1Clock
hwDs1Clock.description: Indicates the clock mode of the interface. master: indicates that the clock works in master mode and uses the internal clock signal. slave: indicates that the clock works in slave mode and uses the line clock signal.

hwDs1FrameFormat.name: hwDs1FrameFormat
hwDs1FrameFormat.description: Indicates the frame format of the interface. crc4: indicates that the frame format is CRC4. no-crc4: indicates that the frame format is no-CRC4. sf: indicates that the frame format is Super Frame. esf: indicates that the frame format is Extended Super Frame. By default, the frame format of an E1 interface is no-crc4. By default, the frame format of a T1 interface is esf.

hwDs1Cable.name: hwDs1Cable
hwDs1Cable.description: The cable command takes effect only if the E1 interface card uses 75-ohm coaxial cable. The default is short. If no cable is connected, this parameter is displayed as null.

hwDs1Loopback.name: hwDs1Loopback
hwDs1Loopback.description: Enable the loopback function of the interface. local: enables the local loopback on the interface. remote: enables the remote loopback on the interface. payload: enables the remote payload loopback on the interface. cell: enables the local cell loopback. The local cell loopback is used to test the local physical chip.

hwDs1ClockRecoveryDomain.name: hwDs1ClockRecoveryDomain
hwDs1ClockRecoveryDomain.description: Indicates the clock recovery domain of the interface.

hwDs1PWClockDomain.name: hwDs1PWClockDomain
hwDs1PWClockDomain.description: Indicates the clock recovery domain of the interface.

hwDs1WorkMode.name: hwDs1WorkMode
hwDs1WorkMode.description: Indicates the clock recovery domain of the interface.

hwDs1EsAlarmTriggerThreshold.name: hwDs1EsAlarmTriggerThreshold
hwDs1EsAlarmTriggerThreshold.description: The trigger threshold of code violation count threshold crossing alarm of E1 line side .

hwDs1EsAlarmResumeThreshold.name: hwDs1EsAlarmResumeThreshold
hwDs1EsAlarmResumeThreshold.description: The resume threshold of code violation count threshold crossing alarm of E1 line side .

hwDs1RowStatus.name: hwDs1RowStatus
hwDs1RowStatus.description: This variable is used to create or delete an object.

hwDs1Lbo.name: hwDs1Lbo
hwDs1Lbo.description: The lbo of T1 port. Unit: db. the value is expanded 10 times,so the real value should be reduced 10 times

hwDs1CableLength.name: hwDs1CableLength
hwDs1CableLength.description: The cableLength of T1 port. Unit: feet.

hwDs3Table.name: hwDs3Table
hwDs3Table.description: This table lists all E3/CE3 interfaces or all T3/CT3 interfaces.

hwDs3Entry.name: hwDs3Entry
hwDs3Entry.description: This table lists all E3/CE3 interfaces or all T3/CT3 interfaces.
